text:
Washington Street, south from Park Place showing this thoroughfare prior to street car track removal. In the foreground are numerous small buildings, housing wholesale firms. To the right is the easterly side of the 29 story N.Y. Telephone Building. (No. 140 West Street). In the background appears the 35 story structure bearing No's 21 Rector Street and 16 Washington Street and 88 Greenwich Street.

April 28, 1937

W.P.A.Photo
Five Boroughs Project
